## WHEN TO ADD HEADERS

Add headers to:

- All source code files
- Configuration files
- Scripts
- Stylesheets
- Templates

## WHEN NOT TO ADD HEADERS

Skip headers for:

- Auto-generated files
- package.json, package-lock.json
- .gitignore, .editorconfig
- README.md (use title instead)

## BENEFITS

- Quick identification of file location
- Track when file was last modified
- Helps with debugging and maintenance
- Easy to see file history at a glance

## REMEMBER

- Headers at the **start** of file
- Footers at the **end** of file
- Update "Modified" date on **every edit**
- Use relative path from project root
